HEADWORD: Obduracy
<hw>Ob"du*ra*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The duality or
state of being obdurate; invincible hardness of heart; obstinacy.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Obduracy</xex> and persistency.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The absolute completion of sin in final <qex>obduracy</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Obdurate</ent>⟦br⟧
